name: The Getty
description: Famous, sizable free museum highlighting American & European art, architecture & manicured gardens.

name: The Original Farmers Market
description: Sprawling historic market features a range of trendy shops, restaurants & gourmet grocery purveyors.

name: Universal Studios Hollywood
description: Sprawling amusement park with a cinema theme, featuring rides, restaurants, shops & shows.

name: Griffith Observatory
description: This art deco landmark from 1935 features a high-tech planetarium, public telescopes & city views.

name: La Brea Tar Pits
description: Ice Age–fossil excavation site with an adjacent museum, plus a re-created prehistoric garden.

name: L.A. Live
description: Massive entertainment complex featuring a theater & The Grammy Museum, plus hotels & restaurants.

name: Disneyland
description: Iconic amusement park featuring 8 themed "lands" with rides, shows & costumed characters.

name: Santa Monica Pier
description: Storied seaside destination showcasing a range of shops & cafes, plus an amusement park & aquarium.

name: Hermosa Beach
description: Beach & sunset ocean views, plus public restrooms & fishing.

name: Battleship USS Iowa Museum
description: Storied Navy warship offering kid-friendly tours (from the decks to the Captain’s Cabin) & exhibits.

name: Huntington Chinese Garden
description: Attraction featuring a bridge, waterfall, and pavilions, plus picnic areas.
